==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saint-Simonism
<hw>Saint-Si"mon*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A system of
socialism in which the state owns all the property and the laborer is
entitled to share according to the quality and amount of his work,
founded by <etsep>Saint Simon</etsep> (1760-1825); -- called also
<altname>Saint- Simonianism</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saith</ent>⟦br⟧
